{
  "urn": "cap:gguf;in=media:textable;llm;ml-model;op=generate_text;out=media:textable",
  "command": "run_inference",
  "title": "Generate Text with LLM (GGUF)",
  "cap_description": "Generate text using GGUF models with llama.cpp backend",
  "documentation": "## Purpose\n\nAccepts a raw text prompt and generates a text continuation using a quantized GGUF model via llama.cpp. This is a simpler prompt-in / text-out interface. Offers more sampling controls than the Candle equivalent (top-k, min-p, repetition penalty, context length).\n\n## Inputs\n\n- A text prompt (plain text).\n- A GGUF model spec (HuggingFace repo or local path). Defaults to Mistral-7B-Instruct Q8_0.\n- Sampling parameters: max tokens (512), temperature (0.7), top-k (40), top-p (0.9), min-p (0.05), repetition penalty (1.1), seed (42), max context length (4096), batch size (2048).\n\n## Outputs\n\nGenerated text streamed as raw text chunks (not NDJSON).\n\n## Notes\n\n- For structured output, system prompts, or streaming JSON events, use [LLM Text Generation (GGUF)](https://capdag.com/browse/cap:gguf;in=\"media:llm-generation-request;json;record\";llm;ml-model;op=llm_inference;out=\"media:llm-text-stream;ndjson\") instead.\n- Increase context length and batch size for long-form generation with large prompts.\n",
  "metadata": {},
